If contacted in relation to a job opportunity, please advise Ciena of any accommodation measures you may require.

Ciena is committed to our people-first philosophy. Our teams enjoy a culture focused on prioritizing a personalized and flexible work environment that empowers an individual’s passions, growth, wellbeing and belonging. We’re a technology company that leads with our humanity—driving our business priorities alongside meaningful social, community, and societal impact.

This role is ideally Ottawa, Ontario, Canada or San Jose, California based however remote in North America is also available.

****************************************************************************

What will you do at Ciena as a Senior Product Line Architect – Security?

The Routing and Switching Portfolio group has an opening for a Principal Engineer within the Product Line Architecture team. In this role you will be a key leader in this small, energetic team, driving the product requirements for routing and switching products, especially in the area of security.

To be successful you will have worked with product management, sales account teams, and customers to both understand their use cases and market requirements in order to guide the customer to solutions which most effectively utilize Ciena’s capabilities.

If you have a passion to author requirements which articulate to engineering general market needs as well as specific customer use cases this will be the right role for you.

As part of your past experience, you have facilitated pragmatic coordination between engineering teams and product management on roadmaps, requirements details, and specific deployment challenges.

The Responsibilities:

Provide leadership as key product line architect for security and other key aspects of our routing and switching products;
Participate in product definition and architecture, and support engineering teams in design, scoping, planning, implementation, and test;
Work closely with key customers to develop solutions that address their immediate and future needs;
Be a subject matter expert, keeping abreast of industry trends and innovations, and use that expertise to guide product managers and senior management team;
Deliver detailed functional requirements and influence technical designs for packet switching software architectures and network management;
Work with Product Line Management team to assess strategic market directions and customer requirements;
Present Ciena solutions to a variety of internal and external audiences, including senior management and technical/operational leads.

What technical experience and personal skills are required for this role?

10+ Years of relevant experience in senior roles in software/systems engineering and/or technical product management;
Master’s or Bachelor’s degree in telecommunications, computer science or a related discipline;
Product design and delivery experience with network equipment and management systems designed for Service Provider deployments;
Experience in documenting customer use cases and technical requirements.
Full understanding of computer security fundamentals, including AAA, X.509/PKI, SSH, TLS, etc.;
Deep knowledge of network and network equipment security mechanisms, including TACACS+/RADIUS, TPM, IPsec, MACsec, 802.1x, firewalls, ACLs, IPS, etc.;
Experience with Common Criteria and FIPS and general requirements for security testing and certification;
Knowledge of network configuration and management, including YANG data modeling and NETCONF, RESTCONF, gNMI, and OpenConfig;
Knowledge of network performance monitoring, telemetry, and troubleshooting;
Practical experience with carrier-class data network deployments, including solution details regarding system security, network management, and service assurance;
Ability to interact effectively with customers, vendors, and internal cross-functional teams and to work across geographies and time zones;
Leadership to independently take initiative while still working collaboratively within the product architecture team, demonstrating good judgment in generating and evaluating alternative approaches to address business and technical challenges;
Excellent verbal and written communications skills.

#LI-FH

#LI-Remote

At Ciena, we are committed to building and fostering an environment in which our employees feel respected, valued, and heard. Ciena values the diversity of its workforce and respects its employees as individuals. We do not tolerate any form of discrimination.

If contacted in relation to a job opportunity, please advise Ciena of any accommodation measures you may require.

Ciena is committed to our people-first philosophy. Our teams enjoy a culture focused on prioritizing a personalized and flexible work environment that empowers an individual’s passions, growth, wellbeing and belonging. We’re a technology company that leads with our humanity—driving our business priorities alongside meaningful social, community, and societal impact.

Ciena may well be the most important technology company you’ve never heard of. The innovations that wow us (driverless cars), and those we now take for granted (the ability to mobile-stream your favorite show) are the products of ingenuity from some brilliant and forward-thinking companies. But those companies rely on Ciena, another vanguard of innovation, to create and advance the underlying networks that bring their breakthroughs to our doorsteps. VR, AI, IOT, 5G … literally none of it would be possible without the mind-boggling technology that makes the internet itself work. For more than 25 years, Ciena has been the global leader in networking strategy, and our technology has been part of the critical infrastructure running within the most advanced companies in the world.

What will you do at Ciena?

You will join the of the Analytics group in Operations, where you will be developing, building, troubleshooting, and supporting data quality, data pipelines and data acquisition systems used in Ciena’s production lines. New data analytics tools and new test systems are required for the next generation of manufacturing, to grow our manufacturing capabilities, which is deployed all around the globe, at the sites of our manufacturing partners.

We want to hire professionals who aspire to work on world-class challenges. We will consider intermediate and senior candidates with skills in data science, software engineering, and/or automation in digital processes. We are breaking ground on new and interesting challenges brought in with our new manufacturing drive (Industry 4.0).

Responsibilities

Create and maintain optimal data pipeline architecture;
Assemble large, complex data sets for our different cross-functional teams;
Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements: automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery,
Transform data for the different set of analytics tools;
Work with other test engineering teams to deliver data and analytical results fast;
Maintain security over our data;
Create data tools for analytics and data scientist team members that assist manufacturing for rapid predictive analysis and pattern matching;

Desired Characteristics

Team player able to effectively collaborate with cross functional teams around the world
Self-motivated, well-organized with a willingness to learn.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
Knowledge of instrumentation, optics, or telecommunication
Experience working with Manufacturing Execution Systems (MES)
Ability to effectively manage multiple priorities and meet aggressive deadlines while maintaining quality of deliverables.
Curiosity to experiment with new technologies, to solve current problems.
Ability to become proficient in new programming languages quickly.
Ability and willingness to travel abroad occasionally.

Collaboration

Daily collaboration with team members, and frequent interactions with Operations, R&D, and Quality engineers.
Supervision of co-op students and research students from universities;
Frequent interactions with various team managers, internet security specialists, contract manufacturers;
Connect with other analytics team and move forward the advanced analytics at Ciena

Technical Knowledge

Apache Spark;
Cloud computing (AWS, Azure)
Scala, Python, C#, .Net technologies, Typescript;
SQL over a variety of databases (Snowflake, Snowpark).
Databricks;
Experience applying different machine learning models (MLflow)
Knowledge of version control and continuous integration;

