What will you do at Ciena as a Test & Automation Engineer – IP Routing and Networking?

We believe in the power of people. We are a network strategy and technology company that is motivated by making a difference in people’s lives – their productivity, their creativity, their health and comfort. That’s why our test engineers help sanitize technologies that allow people to do phenomenal things.

We’re looking for a highly motivated, hard-working and expert engineer who is passionate about manual and automation test activities and is ready to assume a leadership position within the team in addressing future projects.

The Responsibilities and Activities:

Engage engineering teams, product line managers and product owners to transform high-level requirements into optimized test coverage;
Develop test strategies to fully exercise Packet Optical Transport product; System level, Routing and Switching, Provisioning, Performance and Scale, Fault management, Network traffic integrity;
Execution and Delivery of manual and automation end-to-end feature testing, tracking testing using Agile. Due diligence to ensure complete feature coverage, availability of required test environment (i.e., traffic generators, cards, system set up and ready), and the testing is within given quality parameters;
Analyze test results and prepare test reports;
Investigate software defects, highlight critical issues, and collaborate with software development engineers in finding a resolution;
Lead the effort to automate all manual test cases using automation standard methodologies;
Share your vast experience while mentoring more junior members of the team;
You will be the local domain authority for the features you are testing; related standards knowledge and customer requirements;
Provide support for Field Engineers through software upgrades, execution of the assigned test cases, debugging and collecting log files;
From time to time, ownership of internal/external customer prototype demonstration. Assist in standardization and interoperability lab testing;
Develop customer deliverable requirement use cases. Interact with PLM, architects and release managers to harden requirements. Understand the landscape of competitive usage of a feature;
Contribute to IETF and company's intellectual properties (Patents, White papers). Watch for industry standards and data application trends & alert senior management of potential roadblocks in product development.

What technical experience and personal skills are required for this role?

BS/MS degree in Computer Science/Electrical Engineering or equivalent;
7+ years of progressive experience in System & Networking Testing role;
Experience with one or more general purpose programming languages including but not limited to: Java, C/C++, C#, Objective C, Python, JavaScript, or Go;
Interest and ability to learn other coding languages as needed;
Experience in development environments – GIT, Jenkins, Perforce, Clearcase, etc;
Experience working in Agile and Waterfall models of development;
Experience in both manual and automated testing environments;
Excellent troubleshooting and problem-solving skills associated with service provider, enterprise and carrier software solutions in general;
Excellent written (documentation) and interpersonal communication skills (English);
Strong desire and abilities to work as part of a team or independently with little supervision;
Strong abilities to rapidly learn new sophisticated technological concepts and apply knowledge in daily activities;
Experience working with UNIX/Linux/RHEL/Ubuntu and/or any other server OS, be it on bare metal and/or Virtual Machine, and system admin functions;
Knowledge of system level, Layer 2 and Layer 3 protocols (like MPLS, IGP, BGP, Segment Routing, EVPN etc);
Validated experience with Python, Java, JavaScripting, CORBA, TCL/TK/Expect, Oracle, WebLogic and/or REST API and associated tools is highly desirable;
Knowledge and/or work experience related to network virtualization software like Open vSwitch, vRouter, etc. is highly desirable;
Experience working with Layers 2 and/or 3 technologies on Ciena’s CES, 54XX and/or 6500 platforms would be an asset.

